schemas.name: Condition
schemas.desc: Represents a predicate.

fields.name: parameter
fields.desc:
A list of named parameters (key/value), depending on the condition's type. Notes: 
- For binary operators, include parameters named arg0 and arg1 for specifying the left and right operands, respectively. 
- At this time, the left operand (arg0) must be a reference to a variable. 
- For case-insensitive Regex matching, include a boolean parameter named ignore_case that is set to true. If not specified or set to any other value, the matching will be case sensitive. 
- To negate an operator, include a boolean parameter named negate boolean parameter that is set to true.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of operator for this condition.

schemas.name: Parameter
schemas.desc: Represents a Google Tag Manager Parameter.

fields.name: key
fields.desc: The named key that uniquely identifies a parameter. Required for top-level parameters, as well as map values. Ignored for list values.

fields.name: list
fields.desc: This list parameter's parameters (keys will be ignored).

fields.name: map
fields.desc: This map parameter's parameters (must have keys; keys must be unique).

fields.name: type
fields.desc:
The parameter type. Valid values are: 
- boolean: The value represents a boolean, represented as 'true' or 'false' 
- integer: The value represents a 64-bit signed integer value, in base 10 
- list: A list of parameters should be specified 
- map: A map of parameters should be specified 
- template: The value represents any text; this can include variable references (even variable references that might return non-string types)

fields.name: value
fields.desc: A parameter's value (may contain variable references such as "{{myVariable}}") as appropriate to the specified type.

schemas.name: Trigger
schemas.desc: Represents a Google Tag Manager Trigger

fields.name: interval
fields.desc: Time between triggering recurring Timer Events (in milliseconds). Only valid for Timer triggers.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Trigger display name.

fields.name: customEventFilter
fields.desc: Used in the case of custom event, which is fired iff all Conditions are true.

fields.name: eventName
fields.desc: Name of the GTM event that is fired. Only valid for Timer triggers.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: Defines the data layer event that causes this trigger.

fields.name: waitForTagsTimeout
fields.desc: How long to wait (in milliseconds) for tags to fire when 'waits_for_tags' above evaluates to true. Only valid for Form Submission and Link Click triggers.

fields.name: autoEventFilter
fields.desc: Used in the case of auto event tracking.

fields.name: containerId
fields.desc: GTM Container ID.

fields.name: limit
fields.desc: Limit of the number of GTM events this Timer Trigger will fire. If no limit is set, we will continue to fire GTM events until the user leaves the page. Only valid for Timer triggers.

fields.name: parentFolderId
fields.desc: Parent folder id.

fields.name: uniqueTriggerId
fields.desc: Globally unique id of the trigger that auto-generates this (a Form Submit, Link Click or Timer listener) if any. Used to make incompatible auto-events work together with trigger filtering based on trigger ids. This value is populated during output generation since the tags implied by triggers don't exist until then. Only valid for Form Submit, Link Click and Timer triggers.

fields.name: waitForTags
fields.desc: Whether or not we should delay the form submissions or link opening until all of the tags have fired (by preventing the default action and later simulating the default action). Only valid for Form Submission and Link Click triggers.

fields.name: checkValidation
fields.desc: Whether or not we should only fire tags if the form submit or link click event is not cancelled by some other event handler (e.g. because of validation). Only valid for Form Submission and Link Click triggers.

fields.name: enableAllVideos
fields.desc: Reloads the videos in the page that don't already have the YT API enabled. If false, only capture events from videos that already have the API enabled. Only valid for YouTube triggers.

fields.name: fingerprint
fields.desc: The fingerprint of the GTM Trigger as computed at storage time. This value is recomputed whenever the trigger is modified.

fields.name: triggerId
fields.desc: The Trigger ID uniquely identifies the GTM Trigger.

fields.name: videoPercentageList
fields.desc: List of integer percentage values. The trigger will fire as each percentage is reached in any instrumented videos. Only valid for YouTube triggers.

fields.name: accountId
fields.desc: GTM Account ID.

fields.name: filter
fields.desc: The trigger will only fire iff all Conditions are true.

schemas.name: Tag
schemas.desc: Represents a Google Tag Manager Tag.

fields.desc: Firing rule IDs. A tag will fire when any of the listed rules are true and all of its blockingRuleIds (if any specified) are false.

fields.desc: Parent folder id.

fields.name: priority
fields.desc: User defined numeric priority of the tag. Tags are fired asynchronously in order of priority. Tags with higher numeric value fire first. A tag's priority can be a positive or negative value. The default value is 0.

fields.name: blockingRuleId
fields.desc: Blocking rule IDs. If any of the listed rules evaluate to true, the tag will not fire.

fields.name: scheduleEndMs
fields.desc: The end timestamp in milliseconds to schedule a tag.

fields.desc: The start timestamp in milliseconds to schedule a tag.

fields.name: setupTag
fields.desc: The list of setup tags. Currently we only allow one.
